Truly amazed by the takeaway packaging! It looked organized and unique!

The food itself was delightful. I enjoyed the nasi lemak and the sambal, which were both delicious, and the portion sizes were just right. The drinks also had a unique tasteðŸŒ¸

Pretty good, food quality is quite good. Itâ€™s a very small seating area, so seats are limited, especially during lunch hour. Online menu ordering and payment is easy. Nice place for a coffee or a quick meal.

would you pay for nasi lemak (1 chicken wing) ayam mera for 12.90. My husband order nasi lemak (1 chicken wing) and I cost 6.50. The difference between mine and his is the sauce. So effectively, the sauce cost $6.40. It is a total rip off. I will never go back to them again. i can get the same nasi lemak with ayam mera chicken (which is bigger) in red ginger  (IMM) at about $8.

There is no doubt the price was clearly stated  but I was shocked I paid $6.40 for the sauce.

Affordably priced and good food! Have tried the nasi lemak, maggi goreng, nasi goreng and no misses so far.
My mom also says the mee siam is the best she has ever had.
